        'Measurement-based care is the systematic use of standardized measures to track client progress throughout treatment and to use that data to inform clinical decision-making. It is not a treatment modality, not a theoretical orientation, and not a replacement for clinical judgment. Think of it as adding a feedback loop to whatever you already do — a way to check whether your clinical impressions align with what the data shows about how your client is actually doing.',
