        'The technology that genuinely reduces therapist burnout shares a common design philosophy: it eliminates tasks rather than adding features. The distinction is critical. A tool that adds a dashboard full of client data is not inherently helpful if the therapist must now spend time reviewing and interpreting that data. A tool that surfaces the two or three most clinically relevant insights from that data — requiring no additional analysis from the therapist — is genuinely burden-reducing.',
