        'Data security extends beyond HIPAA compliance to practical considerations about device security, data transmission, and storage duration. Clients should understand where their data is stored, how long it is retained, and what happens to it if they discontinue therapy or stop using the tracking platform. Therapists should use platforms that provide clear data retention policies, enable data deletion at the client\'s request, and do not use client data for purposes beyond the client\'s direct clinical care without explicit additional consent.',
